&lt;h2 id=&#34;Minify-JavaScript&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Minify-JavaScript&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Minify JavaScript&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Minify JavaScript&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The next thing we want to do is that we want to minify the resulting combined JavaScript file.  There are several that you could use.  The one I settled on is &lt;a href=&#34;//www.npmjs.com/package/gulp-uglify&#34;&gt;gulp-uglify&lt;/a&gt;. Install gulp-uglify using&lt;/p&gt;
