&lt;h2 id=&#34;Map-Files&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Map-Files&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Map Files&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Map Files&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once we have all of our files minified, we’ll want some way of being able to see the original source code even though you have a minified file that the site is using.  I’m not going to go into a lot of detail about what a map file is or what it does here.  But if you have a problem on a production server, you are going to want to at least have map files available so you can track the issue down. To create a map file, you’ll want to use &lt;a href=&#34;//www.npmjs.com/package/gulp-sourcemaps&#34;&gt;gulp-sourcemaps&lt;/a&gt;. Install using&lt;/p&gt;
